	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">In <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=128190#p128190" class="postlink">this post</a>, caitsith2 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You might want to move that to another unused mapper slot, as 30 has been used already, by <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/UNROM_512" class="postlink">UNROM 512</a>.  I am going to suggest moving over to Mapper 31.</div><br /><br />I have a couple of questions about UNROM-512, which I post here because I have found no other thread with the answer. I hope rainwarrior does not get offended by this small hijack of the topic (I promise I won't go OT anymore after these <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> )<br /><br />1. am I correct that mapper 30 + no battery in header = unflashable setup, while mapper 30 + battery in header = flashable setup?<br />2. is Battle Kid 2 using the FLASH at all?<br />3. is Study Hall the only program using the board in flashable mode?<br /><br /><strong>[Looks like a perfect place for a split --MOD]</strong>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
