	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>caitsith2</b> [ Tue May 06, 2014 3:36 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Sealie UNROM 512 (retrousb.com)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />1. Correct on both counts.<br /><br />2. Battle Kid 2 is not using the flash at all.  In fact, the only part of the board it is using, in the oversize UxROM bit.  I have however created a <a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/20737085/BK2_flash_save.ips" class="postlink">hack</a> that takes advantage of the flash capability. Taking advantage of it on the real cart, requires modding it though,  (specifically adding the components to enable self-flashing, then actually dumping the cart, applying the IPS, and flashing the changed version back onto the cart.)  (I plan to mod my #31 of 33 LE cart with this. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> )<br /><br />3. Currently, Study hall is the only cart for sale that is using the board in self-flashable setup.  However, the XMAS 2013 cart, which is a different board, is also self-flashable, in exactly the same way.   (The main difference with the XMAS 2013 cart, is that any writes from 8000-BFFF turn on/off LEDs, otherwise, the board functions identically to unrom512.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


